Adult Female</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <b>Montagu's harrier</b> (<i>Circus pygargus</i>) is a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird_migration" title="Bird migration">migratory</a> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird_of_prey" title="Bird of prey">bird of prey</a> of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harrier_(bird)" title="Harrier (bird)">harrier</a> family. Its common name commemorates the British <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_history" title="Natural history">naturalist</a> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Montagu_(naturalist)" title="George Montagu (naturalist)">George Montagu</a>.</p>
<p></p>
